records.addlTxt:
Defendant Freddie Montrail Lewis in court with attorney Gary R Schmaus.  Brittany Skye Kachingwe appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court finds State has complied with victim notification. Sentencing hearing proceeded. Statements made as to sentencing. 

AS TO COUNT 1: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS (CONCURRENT TO COUNT 2), with credit for 6 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. 

AS TO COUNT 2: The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 3 YEARS (CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1), with credit for 6 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 2 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 1 YEAR. 

The defendant IS NOT eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and IS eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".

AS TO BOTH COUNTS, the Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of 2 YEARS.  
Court orders the following conditions of probation and extended supervision: 
*No possession of weapons;
*No illegal drugs;
*No alcohol;
*No prescription medication without a valid prescription;
*No new offenses;
*Cooperate with any other terms and conditions deemed appropriate by agent.  

Court orders restitution set at $0.
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs.
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges.   
As to payment of costs and surcharges, Court orders those amounts to be deducted from any bail on deposit.  Remaining balance to be paid during the period of probation.  Any unpaid amount to convert to a civil judgment.  

Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm.
Court advised defendant that his voting rights are suspended and he may not vote in any election until his civil rights are restored. 
Court advised defendant of his right to seek post conviction relief.

Filed,
Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence;
Ineligible Voting Notice/Acknowledgement;
